x4freetext: THERMAL-NEUTRON CAPTURE-GAMMA SPECTRUM OF PU-242
OMEGA WEST REACTOR
APPROXIMATE MAXWELLIAN DISTRIBUTION CORRESPONDING TO
350 DEGREES KELVIN AND A PROBABLE VELOCITY OF
2400-METERS/SEC.
IRREGULARLY SHAPED SAMPLE OF 1 TO 3-MM DIMENSION, 106
MILLIGRAMS IN MASS, 99.9% 242PU.  SAMPLE SEALED
BETWEEN TWO 2-CM DIAMETER DISKS OF 0.25-MM THICK LEAD.
ENTIRE ASSEMBLY HELD IN GRAPHITE HOLDER.
APPROVED BY E.T.JURNEY, 81/9/13.

x4freetext: GERMANIUM-LITHIUM DETECTOR WITH SURROUNDING
ANNULUS HALVES CONNECTED TOGETHER.
THERMAL NEUTRONS, 2223-KEV
LINE OF HYDROGEN CAPTURE GAMMAS USED TO NORMALIZE THE
287.5-KEV LINE FROM SAMPLE.
CO-56 AND NA-24 USED TO CALIBRATE DETECTOR EFFICIENCY
IN ANTICOINCIDENCE MODE
N-14 CAPTURE USED TO CALIBRATE DETECTOR EFFICIENCY IN
DOUBLE ESCAPE MODE
ENERGY CALIBRATION IN ANTICOINCIDENCE MODE DETERMINED
WITH PU(K-ALPHA) X-RAY, POSITRON ANIHILLATION, CO-60
GAMMAS, AL-28 GAMMAS, AND THE 2223-KEV LINE FROM
HYDROGEN NEUTRON CAPTURE
ENERGY CALIBRATION IN DOUBLE ESCAPE MODE DETERMINED
WITH NEUTRON CAPTURE LINES OF C-12 AND HYDROGEN.
DETECTOR USED IN TWO MODES- ANTICOINCIDENCE FOR GAMMAS
OF 100-2400 KEV, AND DOUBLE ESCAPE FOR ENERGIES FROM
2200-5000 KEV. A 44.2 MILLIGRAM SAMPLE OF CH(2)
PLACED IN TARGET POSITION AND SIMULTANEOUS MEASURE-
MENTS MADE IN ORDER TO NORMALIZE THE PU 287.5-KEV LINE
TO THE HYDROGEN 2223-KEV LINE.
CORRECTIONS MADE FOR NON-LINEARITY OF SPECTROMETER
SYSTEM AND FOR GAMMA INTENSITY ATTENUATION DUE TO
SAMPLE SELF ABSORPTION AND ABSORPTION IN LEAD, AIR,
AND LIF.
QUOTED INTENSITY ERRORS CONSIST OF STATISTICAL ERRORS
COMBINED IN QUADRATURE WITH AN ESTIMATED 10 PERCENT
ERROR DUE TO DETECTOR EFFICIENCY AT 287.5-KEV AND
2223-KEV USED IN NORMALIZATION.
ERRORS ALSO DUE TO IRREGULAR SHAPE OF SAMPLE.
